## AI Tell Avoidance

### Sentence Openers to Avoid

- "Additionally," / "Furthermore," / "Moreover," at sentence start
- "Critically, however" / "Notably," / "Importantly,"
- "This [noun] [verb]s" patterns ("This finding suggests...")
- "It is worth noting that..." / "It bears mentioning..."

### Structure Patterns to Avoid

- Em-dash overuse (multiple per paragraph)
- "One is... A second is... A third is..." enumeration
- Artificial three-item lists (padding to rule-of-three)
- "Not only... but also..." constructions
- "Despite these challenges..." openers
- "In conclusion / In summary / Overall" (formulaic endings)

### Language Patterns to Avoid

- "Our results suggest that" (when identification is credible, say "We find")
- "Is consistent with" (weak—be direct)
- Overuse of: "arguably," "potentially," "plausibly"
- "utilize" → always use "use"
- Nominalizations: "make a calculation" → "calculate"

### AI Vocabulary (flag when overused)

align, crucial, delve, elaborate, emphasize, enhance, enduring, foster, garner, highlight, intricate, interplay, pivotal, showcase, tapestry, underscore, leverage, robust, nuanced, multifaceted, comprehensive, facilitate

